        text: 'Elizabeth Holmes set out to revolutionize the medical industry. Her invention was supposed to transform diagnostics. Instead, she became infamous for running a large scale scam. She built her empire on lies. Her promises drew in investors, and the customers who trusted her paid the price in their health, because the promises were never kept.\n\nAspirations are not wrong, but we cannot put other people lives at risk in pursuit of our dreams. We have to stay human and treat people as equals. Elizabeth Holmes let the power go to her head. She hired a team of yes men and fired anyone who tried to show her the reality she was in. Aspiring leaders should learn from this story. Having people around you who can tell you the truth and question your beliefs is essential. They keep you grounded.\n\nMost importantly, you have to be kind. Walking over people might get you somewhere, but you will not stay there for long. Your methods matter as much as your goals. And once the truth comes to light, the fall comes soon. Dishonest athletes lose their medals, and lying CEOs go to jail.\n\nIt takes courage to expose fraud, especially when billions of dollars are at stake. A person with a strong value system, though, will have little trouble choosing to pursue the truth. What are your values? Take some time to write down the character traits that matter most to you, no matter what you do or where you are.\n\nKeep reading to the end.',
